The paper discusses the performance of randomly weighted neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The focus is on image classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of an algorithm to find the subnetworks, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
